obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act and the Statutes, the Ordinances of the`
  line `Institute may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the admission of the students to the Institute;`
  line
  line `(b) the reservation for the Scheduled Castes, the Scheduled Tribes and other backward categories`
  line `of persons;`
  line
  line `(c) the courses of study to be laid down for all degrees, diplomas and certificates of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(d) the conditions under which students shall be admitted to the degree, diploma and certificate`
  line `courses and to the examinations of the Institute and award of degrees, diplomas and certificates;`
  line
  line `(e) the conditions for award of fellowships, scholarships, exhibitions, medals and prizes;`
  line
  line `(f) the conditions and mode of appointment and duties of examining body, examiners and`
  line moderators;
  line
  line `(g) the conduct of examinations;`
  line
  line `(h) the maintenance of discipline among the students of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(i) the fees to be charged for courses of study in the Institute and for admission to the examinations of`
  line `degrees, diplomas and certificates of the Institute; and`
  line
  line `(j) any other matter which by this Act or the Statutes is to be or may be provided for by the`
  line Ordinances.
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (2267)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Ordinance how made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00011_201720_1517807328050&sectionId=2267&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00011_201720_1517807328050
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this section, Ordinances shall be made`
  line `by the Senate.`
  line
  line `(2) All Ordinances made by the Senate shall have effect from such date as it may direct, but every`
  line `Ordinance so made shall be submitted, as soon as may be, to the Governing Council and shall be considered`
  line `by the Governing Council at its next succeeding meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) The Governing Council shall have power by resolution to modify or cancel any such Ordinance`
  line `and such Ordinance shall from the date of such resolution stand modified accordingly or cancelled, as the`
  line `case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (2268)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Tribunal of Arbitration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00011_201720_1517807328050&sectionId=2268&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00011_201720_1517807328050
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any dispute arising out of a contract between the Institute and any of`
  line `its employees shall, at the request of the employee concerned or at the instance of the Institute, be referred to`
  line `a Tribunal of Arbitration consisting of one member appointed by the Institute, one member nominated by the`
  line `employee and an umpire appointed by the Visitor.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Tribunal of Arbitration shall be final and shall not be questioned in any court.`
  line
  line `(3) No suit or proceeding shall lie in any court in respect of any matter which is required by`
  line `sub-section (1) to be referred to the Tribunal of Arbitration.`
  line
  line `(4) The Tribunal of Arbitration shall have power to regulate its own procedure.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in any law for the time being in force relating to arbitration shall apply to arbitration under`
  line `this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (2269)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Act and proceedings not to be invalidated by vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00011_201720_1517807328050&sectionId=2269&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00011_201720_1517807328050
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `No act of the Institute or Governing`
  line `Council or Senate or any other body set-up under this Act or the Statutes, shall be invalid merely by`
  line `reason of—`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or defect in the constitution thereof; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the election, nomination or appointment of a person acting as a member thereof;`
  line or
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in its procedure not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (2270)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Sponsored schemes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00011_201720_1517807328050&sectionId=2270&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00011_201720_1517807328050
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, whenever the Institute receives`
  line `funds from any Government, the University Grants Commission or any other agency, including industry`
  line `sponsoring a research scheme or a consultancy assignment or a teaching programme or a chaired professorship`
  line `or a scholarship, etc., to be executed or endowed at the Institute—`
  line
  line `(a) the amount received shall be kept by the Institute separately from the Fund of the Institute and`
  line `utilised only for the purpose of the scheme; and`
  line
  line `(b) the staff required to execute the same shall be recruited in accordance with the terms and`
  line `conditions stipulated by the sponsoring organisations:`
  line
  line `Provided that any money remaining unutilised shall be transferred to the endowment fund created`
  line `under section 22 of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (2271)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Power of Institute to grant degree, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00011_201720_1517807328050&sectionId=2271&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00011_201720_1517807328050
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `The Institute shall have the power to grant degrees,`
  line `diplomas, certificates and other academic distinctions under this Act, which shall be equivalent to such`
  line `corresponding degrees, diplomas, certificates and other academic distinctions granted by any University or`
  line `Institute established or incorporated under any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (2272)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Institute to be public authority under the Right to Information Act, 2005.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00011_201720_1517807328050&sectionId=2272&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00011_201720_1517807328050
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of`
  line `the Right to Information Act, 2005 (22 of 2005) shall apply to the Institute, as if it were a public authority`
  line `as defined in clause (h) of section 2 of the Right to Information Act, 2005.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (2273)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00011_201720_1517807328050&sectionId=2273&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00011_201720_1517807328050
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of appointment of the Managing Director, Secretary and Executive Director and`
  line `terms and conditions of his services;`
  line
  line `(b) the terms and conditions of service of the Managing Director, Secretary and the Executive`
  line `Director under sub-section (1) of section 16, sub-section (1) of section 17 and sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 18;`
  line
  line `(c) the form and manner in which the books of account of the Institute shall be maintained under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 23; and`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House`
  line `of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or`
  line `in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session`
  line `or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses`
  line `agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without`
  line `prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (2274)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Returns and information to be provided to Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00011_201720_1517807328050&sectionId=2274&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00011_201720_1517807328050
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `The Institute shall furnish to the`
  line `Central Government such returns or other information with respect to policies or activities as the Central`
  line `Government may, for the purpose of reporting to Parliament or for the making of policy, from time to time,`
  line require.
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (2275)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00011_201720_1517807328050&sectionId=2275&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00011_201720_1517807328050
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act—`
  line
  line `(a) the Governing Council of the Society functioning as such, immediately before the commencement`
  line `of this Act shall continue to so function until a new Governing Council is constituted for the Institute under`
  line `this Act, but on the constitution of a new Governing Council under this Act the members of the Governing`
  line `Council holding office before such constitution shall cease to hold office;`
  line
  line `(b) until the first Statutes and the Ordinances are made under this Act, the rules and regulations,`
  line `instructions and guidelines of the Society as in force, immediately before the commencement of this`
  line `Act, shall continue to apply to the Institute insofar as they are not inconsistent with the provisions of`
  line `this Act; and`
  line
  line `(c) any student who joined classes of the existing Institute on or after the academic year 2012-2013 or`
  line `completed the course on or after the academic year 2013-2014 shall for the purposes of clause (iii) of section 7,`
  line `be deemed to have pursued a course of study in the existing Institute if such student has not already been awarded`
  line `degree or diploma for the same course of study.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (2276)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Statute and Ordinance to be published in the Official Gazette and to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00011_201720_1517807328050&sectionId=2276&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00011_201720_1517807328050
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Statute or Ordinance made under this Act shall be published in the Official`
  line Gazette.
  line
  line `(2) Every Statute or Ordinance made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in`
  line `the Statute or Ordinance or both Houses agree that the Statute or Ordinance should not be made, the Statute or`
  line `Ordinance shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so,`
  line `however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything`
  line `previously done under that Statute or Ordinance.`
  line
  line `(3) The power to make Statutes or Ordinances shall include the power to give retrospective effect with`
  line `the approval of the Central Government from a date not earlier than the date of commencement of this Act`
  line `to Statutes or Ordinances or any of them but no retrospective effect shall be given to any Statute or`
  line `Ordinance so as to prejudicially affect the interests of any person to whom such Statutes or Ordinances may`
  line `be applicable.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (2277)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00011_201720_1517807328050&sectionId=2277&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00011_201720_1517807328050
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) lf any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provision or`
  line `give such direction not inconsistent with the purposes of this Act, as appears to it to be necessary or`
  line `expedient for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of two years from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
